HEADWORD: cowpoke
<hw>cowpoke</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a hired hand who tends cattle and
performs other duties on horseback; -- an informal name for
<altname>cowboy</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cowboy, cowpuncher, puncher, cowman, cattleman,
cowhand, cowherd.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

